text: George James Pallett (1907-1996) was a male athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== He competed for England in the long jump at the 1934 British Empire Games in London. Pallett was a president of the Herne Hill Harriers and was a qualified AAA coach in all field events. ==References== Category:1907 births Category:1996 deaths Category:English male long jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1934 British Empire Games
